			</div><div class="blogs_commententrybody">
				Why was Mike the center of the investigation?  Well, elementary, my dear Watson, in interviewing one of the employees, she said:

"Chief, Mike is a CPA. He did it all." 

Now, if that doesn't point a finger, the other clue was that Mike was the one pointing to Dana the entire time.  Mark simply followed Mike's lead.

The 'lucrative lure'???  I'm wondering if those fake companies that were paid are shell companies set up by Mike to siphon off the cash so he can go into business by himself.  Brothers going into business together is one thing - brothers doing _everying_
in life together is entirely another and Mike probably saw an opportunity to take advantage of Mark.

My two cents.


