				</div>
			</div><div class="blogs_commententrybody">
				The Lucrative Lure? All that lovely money with a built-in culprit to take the fall.
Why Mike?  He had the authority, aptitude and the system access required.  He "always did the financial work (pt VI)" before Dana was employed. 
Early evidence - the repeated mention of a shiny Rolex on one of the brothers wrists.  
Other hints: The thousands of dollars of errors were spotted by a temp book-keeper during a simple reconciliation but missed repeatedly by a CPA who knew the books, clients and suppliers? Not likely!
Dana was both lucky and smart to get out of this intact.


			</div>
